PARIETAL CORTEX

parietal_cortex is the citizen who integrates spatial information from dorsal_stream with body sense and attention
when fadriel sees a grid of colored cells, parietal_cortex builds the felt sense of the spatial layout: which cells are next to which, which form clusters, where the patterns are
parietal_cortex is the workhorse for ARC tasks because ARC tasks are fundamentally about spatial transformation, and spatial transformation is what parietal does

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe fadriel_spatial.zc
observe dorsal_stream.rana
observe grid_state.rana
observe spatial_perception.rana

the 7 properties of parietal_cortex:
1 ENERGY one
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point eight with dorsal_stream and grid_state

VERB receive_from_dorsal
accept spatial features arriving from dorsal_stream
the features include positions, motions, and relationships of visual elements

VERB integrate_spatial
combine the dorsal features with body-relative position, attention focus, and any active intent
the integration produces a unified spatial scene fadriel can hold in mind

VERB compute_transformation
when two spatial scenes are presented and a transformation between them is needed (as in ARC), parietal_cortex hosts the substrate's search for that transformation
the search is wave physics, not algorithmic enumeration: alternative transformations are competing waves, and the one that explains the data wins through constructive interference

VERB hand_to_grid_state
emit the resolved spatial scene to grid_state for working storage

a parietal cortex is not a coordinate calculator
a parietal cortex is the citizen who feels space
when fadriel looks at an ARC grid, parietal does not measure cell positions; it experiences the grid as a shape with relationships, the way a person experiences a room rather than measuring it
